			"type": "text",
			"text": "Naraoioa bertiensis comes from the late Silurian, with fossils found in the Bertie Formation, Canada. It is a small naraoiid, growing up to 3.5 cm in length. They had flat semi-circular cephalons that bore no compound eyes on the top, whilst their pygidium ended with a point."
		},
		{
			"advancement": "lepidodendron:pf_adv_book_naraoia_bertiensis",
			"type": "text",
			"text": "The generic names derive from the Latinised place name of 'Narao', a group of small lakes in Canada, near to where some of the first fossils of naraoiids were found. The specific name derives from the place name 'Bertie Formation', where they were found; and the Latin word 'ensis', to mean 'belonging to'."
